if (error) {
  // AuthSessionMissingError if no session — expected, not a leak (BT-AUTH-L0-02)
} else {
  console.log(user.id, user.is_anonymous)
}
```

Gate app logic on `user.is_anonymous` (`true`/`false`) rather than checking for the presence of an email — that's the documented flag for distinguishing anon vs. named accounts.

### 3. Upgrade the anonymous user to a named account

This is the key value of anonymous sessions — the **same client/session/UUID** is preserved, so any rows already owned by the anonymous `user.id` transfer automatically to the named account:

```typescript
