Supabase's Storage server implements the [tus protocol](https://tus.io/) at:

```
POST https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/storage/v1/upload/resumable
```

The supported client library is **`tus-js-client`** (not `supabase-js` directly — `supabase-js` has no TUS API as of v2.x). Per [6], this endpoint accepts either the `service_role` key or an authenticated user's JWT in `Authorization: Bearer <token>`, and **RLS still applies** to the final insert into `storage.objects` — so an anon-key upload to an RLS-protected bucket will complete the TUS handshake but fail the row insert.

