# Pattern: Image transform on download (resize, format, quality) via Smart CDN

**Status:** Live verified at L3 BT-L3-07..10 and Capstone BT-CAP-07. This is a **paid feature** — must be gated with an availability probe before relying on it in tests or production logic.

## When to use

You have image files (PNG, JPEG, WebP) in Supabase Storage and want server-side resizing / format conversion / quality adjustment at fetch time, without standing up a separate image-processing service.

## 1. Availability gate (do this first)

Transforms return 4xx on free-tier projects. Probe at suite setup and skip downstream assertions if unavailable:

```typescript
let TRANSFORMS_AVAILABLE: boolean | null = null;

it('probe transforms', async () => {
  const url = supabase.storage.from(PUB_BUCKET)
    .getPublicUrl('img.png', { transform: { width: 50 } }).data.publicUrl;
  const res = await fetch(url);
  TRANSFORMS_AVAILABLE = res.status === 200;
});
```

(On the Wave 5b test project, transforms WERE available — all L3 transform BTs returned 200.)

## 2. Public URL transform (resize / resize mode / format)

```typescript
const { data } = supabase.storage
  .from(PUB_BUCKET)
  .getPublicUrl('img.png', {
    transform: { width: 200, height: 200 } // resize: 'cover' | 'contain' | 'fill'; format: 'webp'
  });
```

- `transform: { width: 200, height: 200 }` → status 200, `content-type: image/png`, URL contains literal `width=200&height=200` query params. [BT-L3-07]
- `resize: 'cover' | 'contain' | 'fill'` → all return 200, all `image/png`. [BT-L3-08]
- `format: 'webp'` → status 200, `content-type: image/webp`. [BT-L3-09]

## 3. Signed-URL transform (private buckets — params ride in the JWT, NOT the query string)

```typescript
const { data } = await supabase.storage
  .from(PRIV_BUCKET)
  .createSignedUrl('img.png', 60, { transform: { width: 64, height: 64 } });
// data.signedUrl contains /render/image/sign/ but NOT width=... in the query
```

Verified: `createSignedUrl` + `{ transform: { width:64, height:64 } }` → 200, `image/png`, URL contains `/render/image/sign/`. [BT-CAP-07]

The URL routes through `/storage/v1/render/image/sign/<bucket>/<path>?token=<jwt>`, and the `transformations` claim **inside the JWT** carries the actual params — do not expect (or assert on) `width=`/`height=` in the query string here, unlike the public-URL case. See `gotcha-signed-url-transform-jwt-claims-not-query.md`.

## What to assert in tests

```typescript
const res = await fetch(transformedUrl);
expect(res.status).toBe(200);
expect(res.headers.get('content-type')).toMatch(/^image\//);
const bytes = Buffer.from(await res.arrayBuffer());
expect(bytes.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);
```

For format conversion, assert the exact content-type:
```typescript
expect(res.headers.get('content-type')).toBe('image/webp');
```

## Known pitfall: quality assertions need a real fixture

Do NOT test `quality: 20` vs `quality: 90` against a 1×1 PNG fixture — both come back as identical 283-byte payloads (degenerate case, tracked as Gap #26 in the corpus). Use a fixture whose dimensions are ≥ your transform output dims, then assert:

```typescript
// On a tiny fixture, use <=. On a large fixture, < is safe.
expect(q20Bytes).toBeLessThanOrEqual(q90Bytes);
```

